<content>
    <chapter line="1">20. Amatavaggavaṇṇanā</chapter>
    <paragraph line="2" number="600-611"> Natthi <pageBreak edition="Vipassana Research Institut" number="1.0270" /> ettha mataṃ maraṇaṃ vināsoti <bold>amataṃ,</bold> nibbānanti āha – <bold>‘‘maraṇavirahitaṃ nibbānaṃ paribhuñjantī’’</bold>ti. Amatassa vā nibbānassa adhigamahetutāya <pageBreak edition="Myanmar" number="1.0288" /> amatasadisaatappakasukhapatitatāya ca kāyagatāsati <bold>‘‘amata’’</bold>nti vuttā. <bold>Paribhuñjantī</bold>ti jhānasamāpajjanena vaḷañjanti. <bold>Viraddha</bold>nti anadhigamena virajjhitaṃ. Tenāha – <bold>‘‘virādhitaṃ nādhigata’’</bold>nti. <bold>Āraddha</bold>nti sādhitaṃ nipphāditaṃ. Tañca paripuṇṇaṃ nāma hotīti āha – <bold>‘‘āraddhanti paripuṇṇa’’</bold>nti. <bold>Pamādiṃsū</bold>ti kālabyattayenedaṃ vuttanti āha – <bold>‘‘pamajjantī’’</bold>ti.</paragraph>
    <centered line="3">Amatavaggavaṇṇanā niṭṭhitā.</centered>
    <centered line="4">Iti manorathapūraṇiyā aṅguttaranikāya-aṭṭhakathāya</centered>
    <centered line="5">Ekakanipātavaṇṇanāya anuttānatthadīpanā samattā.</centered>
    <centered line="6">Paṭhamo bhāgo niṭṭhito.</centered>
